{{ja-kanjitab|yomi=k|つが}}

{{IPAfont|⟨tuɡa⟩}} → {{IPAchar|/t͡suɡa/}}

From {{inh|ja|ojp|sort=つが|-}}.  Found in the ''{{w|Man'yōshū}}'', completed some time after 759 CE.<ref>{{RQ:Manyoshu|3|324}}, text [http://jti.lib.virginia.edu/japanese/manyoshu/Man3Yos.html#324 here]</ref>

Appears to be an alternative phonetic realization of ''toga'' below.

{{der-top}}
* {{ja-r|都%賀|^つ%が}}: a [[surname]] and [[place name]]
* {{ja-r|栂%桜|つが%ざくら}}: {{taxlink|Phyllodoce nipponica|species}}
* {{ja-r|栂の木|つがのき}}: a [[hemlock]] [[tree]]
{{der-bottom}}

{{ja-kanjitab|yomi=k|とが}}

{{IPAfont|⟨to<sub>1</sub>ɡa⟩}} → {{IPAchar|/toɡa/}}
: Alternative reconstruction:
{{IPAfont|⟨to<sub>1</sub>ɡa⟩}} → *{{IPAchar|/twoɡa/}} → {{IPAchar|/toɡa/}}

From {{inh|ja|ojp|sort=とが|-}}.  Found in the ''{{w|Man'yōshū}}'', completed some time after 759 CE.<ref>{{RQ:Manyoshu|6|907}}, text [http://jti.lib.virginia.edu/japanese/manyoshu/Man6Yos.html#907 here]</ref>

Appears to be an alternative phonetic realization of ''tsuga'' above.

{{der-top}}
* {{ja-r|栂%椹|とが%さわら}}: the {{vern|Japanese Douglas fir}} ({{taxlink|Pseudotsuga japonica|species}})
* {{ja-r|栂%尾|^とが%の.お}}: a place in Kyoto
{{der-bottom}}
